  <front>
   <head>COME, MORTALS, ENLIVEN THE HOUR.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="1" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">COME mortals, enliven the hour that is lent,</l>
     <l n="2" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Nor cloud with false fear the sunshine of to-day;</l>
     <l n="3" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">The ills that hang o'er us what sighs can prevent,</l>
     <l n="4" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Or waft from the eye one moist sorrow away?</l>
     <l n="5" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Though we see from afar, as he travels life's road,</l>
     <l n="6" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Old time mowing down both the shrub and the flower,</l>
     <l n="7" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Soon or late, we all know, he must sweep our abode,</l>
     <l n="8" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">But why damp our mirth by inquiring the hour?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="9" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">In the span that's allotted then crowd every joy;</l>
     <l n="10" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Let the goblet run high if in dreams you delight;</l>
     <l n="11" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Though wine to true pleasure is oft an alloy,</l>
     <l n="12" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">And sober reflection grows sick at the sight.</l>
     <l n="13" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Disguis'd are our pleasures, as well as our woes;</l>
     <l n="14" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">On their choice must depend half the turn of our fate;</l>
     <l n="15" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">With the tint of the mind every circumstance glows,</l>
     <l n="16" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">And gives to life's trifles their colour and weight.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
